The paper discusses website fingerprinting attacks and defenses, which are related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also employs machine learning techniques (cs.LG) to derive security bounds for WF defenses. Additionally, the paper discusses the privacy concerns of users (cs.CY) and proposes a method to identify optimal feature sets (cs.SI) for WF defenses. Finally, the paper's approach of deriving security bounds for ML-based attacks could be applicable to other areas of computer science, such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
